getCompareValue

protected java.lang.Comparable getCompareValue(java.lang.Object o)
Tries to get a value from specified object. If the sortByGetter is null DynaBeanUtils.getProperty() is used, Otherwise the predefined sortByGetter is used. This happens if the object is not from exactly the same class as the one the sortByGetter is created from. At last, if the value is instanceof String it is converted to lowercase for case-insensitive sorting

Parameters:
o -
Returns:
the value of the property specified by sortBy of the specified object.

applyFilters

protected java.util.List applyFilters(java.util.List rows)
Applies all filters onto the specified rows. The original list is not changed by this method. It is probably faster to iterate over the rows for every filter as with some luck the first filter will already remove some rows, so further filters have less work.

Parameters:
rows - A list of rows
Returns:
The filtered list of rows (the original list is not changed by this method)
